@page "/endpoint"

<h1>Image Endpoint</h1>

<p>
    The images below are served from <code>/api/skia/&lt;name&gt;</code> — a Minimal API endpoint
    that renders with SkiaSharp and returns WebP. The browser fetches them as normal images.
    Images resize dynamically with the container. The clock animates every second.
</p>

<div class="container">
    <div class="row mb-3">
        <div class="col">
            <h5>Default — <code>/api/skia/default</code></h5>
            <div class="border rounded p-2 canvas-container">
                <img id="dyn-endpoint-default" src="/api/skia/default" class="dynamic-skia-img"
                     alt="SkiaSharp default rendering" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mb-3">
        <div class="col">
            <h5>Circles — <code>/api/skia/circles</code></h5>
            <div class="border rounded p-2 canvas-container">
                <img id="dyn-endpoint-circles" src="/api/skia/circles" class="dynamic-skia-img"
                     alt="SkiaSharp circles rendering" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="row mb-3">
        <div class="col">
            <h5>Clock — <code>/api/skia/clock</code> (animated)</h5>
            <div class="border rounded p-2 canvas-container">
                <img id="dyn-endpoint-clock" src="/api/skia/clock" class="dynamic-skia-img"
                     alt="SkiaSharp clock rendering" />
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
    <strong>How it works:</strong> The <code>/api/skia/&#123;name&#125;?w=WIDTH&amp;h=HEIGHT</code> endpoint in <code>Program.cs</code>
    creates an <code>SKSurface</code>, draws via <code>SkiaRenderer.Draw()</code>, encodes to WebP,
    and returns the bytes. JavaScript watches the container size and re-fetches at the correct
    resolution. The clock polls every second for animation.
</div>

<div class="alert alert-secondary mt-2">
    <strong>Tip:</strong> Try opening <a href="/api/skia/circles" target="_blank">/api/skia/circles</a>
    directly in a new tab — it's just an image URL. Try resizing the browser window!
</div>

<script suppress-error="BL9992">
    function startSkiaDynamic() {
        if (typeof SkiaDynamic === 'undefined') {
            setTimeout(startSkiaDynamic, 50);
            return;
        }
        SkiaDynamic.start('dyn-endpoint-default', 'default', 0, true);
        SkiaDynamic.start('dyn-endpoint-circles', 'circles', 0, true);
        SkiaDynamic.start('dyn-endpoint-clock', 'clock', 1000, true);
    }
    startSkiaDynamic();
</script>
